<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 8: TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER -
        GEAR TRAIN REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>GEAR TRAIN REMOVAL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="4">
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate engine so timing marks on lower and upper idler gears, crankshaft and camshaft
                    gear are aligned (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600815">8.15</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Once assembled at "marks aligned" position, engine will require 37 crankshaft revolutions
                            for "marks aligned" position again.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1600814" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5307" filename="../figeg5/EG5307.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.14 Oil Pressure Relief Valve Location</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Oil Pressure Relief Valve</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600815" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5313" filename="../figeg5/EG5313.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.15 Aligning Timing Marks On Gears</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Crankshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>PRIOR TO REMOVING ANY GEAR, MOUNT A DIAL INDICATOR ONTO THE ENGINE AND CHECK FOR GEAR
                            BACKLASH.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check upper idler gear lash as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600816">8.16</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount magnetic base dial indicator on top of crankcase.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position dial indicator on gear tooth and "zero" indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place a screwdriver between crankshaft and lower idler gear.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Move upper idler gear back and forth.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Record reading on dial indicator. If backlash exceeds specified limits (see
                        <emph type="bold">"SPECIFICATIONS"</emph>), replace upper idler gear.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using dial indicator also check upper idler gear end play.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check lower idler gear lash as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600817">8.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount a magnetic base dial indicator onto front cover.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position dial indicator on gear tooth and "zero" indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Move lower idler gear back and forth</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Record reading on dial indicator. If backlash exceeds specified limits (see
                        <emph type="bold">"SPECIFICATIONS"</emph>), replace lower idler gear.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using dial indicator also check lower idler gear end play.</para>
                <figure id="ef1600816" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5309" filename="../figeg5/EG5309.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.16 Checking Upper Idler Gear Lash</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600817" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5308" filename="../figeg5/EG5308.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.17 Checking Lower Idler Gear Lash</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check camshaft gear end play as follows (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_219.xml" xrefid="ef1600818">8.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount a magnetic base dial indicator to the top of the crankcase.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position dial indicator onto camshaft tooth and "zero" dial indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place a screwdriver between the lower and upper idler gears.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Move the camshaft gear back and forth.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Record reading on dial indicator. If end play exceeds specified limits (see
                        <emph type="bold">"SPECIFICATIONS"</emph>), replace camshaft gear.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using dial indicator also check camshaft gear end play.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Visually inspect all gears for nicks, chips or wear. Replace as necessary.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
